title.narrative: By 2021, improved MOH capacity for EPI

description.narrative: The unprecedented crisis caused by COVID-19 has marked the year 2021, with the country’s immunization programme having had to face disruptions, especially during the lockdown period. Recognizing the country&39;s challenging operating environment, UNICEF significantly increased efforts ensuring the country&39;s immunization programme is maintained. A total of 50 poor-performing districts received UNICEF funding to ensure a continuity of essential health services, particularly immunization. Since the pandemic&39;s longer-term trajectory remains uncertain, as part of UNICEF’s commitment to immunization and health system strengthening, efforts focused on further enhancing the Cold Chain System Strengthening and scale up of the COVID-19 vaccine. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
